				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">But watch out for DPCM double clocks. With a report that long (64 bits), the repeat-and-compare method might not work so well. So the keyboard's circuitry itself would have to smooth out double clocks. I seem to remember MMC3 doing the same thing for PPU A12, which cycles rapidly at the end of each scanline, before it hits the scanline counter.
<br />
<br />An authentic controller reading loop, even an unrolled one, won't clock faster than more than once every 11 CPU cycles, or 163 kHz:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.repeat 8<br />&nbsp; lda $4017<br />&nbsp; lsr a<br />&nbsp; rol 0<br />.endrepeat<br /></div>
<br />Anything faster than that is probably a double clock.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

