					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Wookie wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The real trick would be to figure out a way to detect the presence of a the keyboard adapter from the 2A03.  Maybe there is something we could do with pins 6 and 7 on the controller port to signal that the device plugged into a given controller port is a PS/2 keyboard adapter.  Do any of the other NES peripherals like Rob, power pad, or light gun use those pins?</div>
<br />Seven signals are present on the controller port: 0 V, 5 V, clock, strobe out, data in D0, data in D3, and data in D4. The Zapper uses D3 and D4 for the button state and the photodiode state. The Power Pad uses D3 and D4 much as the standard controller uses D0.</div>

